===Etymology===
Anglo-Norman, from Old Northern French [[wage]], a northern variant of Old French [[guage]], [[gage]], from Old Franconian ''*waddi'' (cognate with Old English [[wedd]]), from Germanic ''*wadja''.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/weɪʤ/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# an amount of money paid to a worker for a specified quantity of [[Wikipedia:Labour (economics)|work]]. usually expressed on an hourly basis.

